  "body": "With `--asm` option the compiler prints not only source locations but also small snippets of the Solidity code from those locations. For example:\r\n\r\n```\r\ntag_5:\r\n    /* \"test.sol\":111:117  uint x */\r\n  0x00\r\n    /* \"test.sol\":120:121  1 */\r\n  0x01\r\n    /* \"test.sol\":111:121  uint x = 1 */\r\n  swap1\r\n  pop\r\n    /* \"test.sol\":101:128  {... */\r\n  pop\r\n    /* \"test.sol\":81:128  function f() public {... */\r\n  jump      // out\r\n```\r\n\r\nIn IR we only get locations:\r\n```yul\r\n/// @src 0:81:128\r\nfunction fun_f_21() {\r\n\r\n    /// @src 0:120:121\r\n    let expr_18 := 0x01\r\n    /// @src 0:111:121\r\n    let var_x_17 := convert_t_rational_1_by_1_to_t_uint256(expr_18)\r\n\r\n}\r\n/// @src 0:0:130\r\n\r\nfunction identity(value) -> ret {\r\n    ret := value\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n`AsmPrinter` should be extended to add snippets in IR too.",
